a |editor2-last =  Michlic |title=Bringing the Dark Past to Light. The Reception of the Holocaust in Postcommunist Europe.|title-link=Bringing the Dark Past to Light |chapter=The \"Unmasterable Past\"? The Reception of the Holocaust in Postcommunist Slovakia|location=Lincoln |publisher=University of Nebraska Press |year=2013 |isbn=978-0-8032-2544-2 |ref=harv |pp=549\u2013590}}\t\n*{{cite encyclopedia|entry=Slovakia|last1=Rothkirchen|first1=Livia |authorlink=Livia Rothkirchen|pp=595\u2013600 |editor1-last=Laqueur |editor1-first=Walter |editor-link=Walter Laqueur|editor2-last=Baumel |editor2-first=Judith Tydor |title=Holocaust Encyclopedia |date=2001 |publisher=Yale University Press |location=New Haven |language=en|isbn=978-0-300-08432-0|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=T\u00f6nsmeyer |first1=Tatjana|authorlink=Tatjana T\u00f6nsmeyer |editor1-last=Dean |editor1-first=Martin|editor1-link=Martin C. Dean |editor2-last=Goschler |editor2-first=Constantin |editor3-last=Ther |editor3-first=Philipp |title=Robbery and Restitution: The Conflict over Jewish Property in Europe |date=2007 |publisher=Berghahn Books |location=New York |isbn=9780857455642 |pages=81\u201396 |ref=harv |language=en |chapter=The Robbery of Jewish Property in Eastern European States Allied with Nazi Germany}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Book reviews====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Cichopek-Gajraj |first1=Anna |title=Nepokrade\u0161! N\u00e1lady a postoje slovensk\u00e9 spole\u010dnosti k \u017eidovsk\u00e9 ot\u00e1zce, 1938\u20131945 [Thou shall not steal! Moods and attitudes of Slovak society toward the Jewish question] |journal=East European Jewish Affairs |date=2018 |volume=48 |issue=2 |pages=253\u2013255 |doi=10.1080/13501674.2018.1505360|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Johnson |first1=Owen V. |title=\u017didovsk\u00e1 komunita na Slovensku medzi ceskoslovenskou parlamentnou demokraciou a slovensk\u00fdm \u0161t\u00e1tom v stredoeur\u00f3pskom kontexte, Eduard Ni\u017enansk\u00fd (Pre\u0161ov, Slovakia: Universum, 1999), 292 pp., 200 crowns (Slovak). |journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies |date=2005 |volume=19 |issue=2 |pages=314\u2013317 |doi=10.1093/hgs/dci033|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Theses====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite thesis|degree=PhD|editor-last=Himka|editor-first=John-Paul|editor-link=John-Paul  Himka |last1=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |first1=Nina |title=Rescue of Jews in the Slovak State (1939\u20131945) |date=2012 |url=https://era.library.ualberta.ca/items/e8340da1-7b46-40cc-95e1-d57665a23e34 |language=en|doi=10.7939/R33H33|institution=[[University of Alberta]]|ref=harv|location=Edmonton}}\n*{{cite thesis|last=Put\u00edk|first=Daniel|title=Sloven\u0161t\u00ed \u017did\u00e9 v Terez\u00edn\u011b, Sachsenhausenu, Ravensbr\u00fccku a Bergen-Belsenu, 1944/1945|language=cs|trans-title=Slovak Jews in Theresienstadt, Sachsenhausen, Ravensbr\u00fcck and Bergen-Belsen, 1944/1945|date=2015|degree=PhD|url=https://is.cuni.cz/webapps/zzp/detail/104422/?lang=en|institution=[[Charles University]]|location=Prague|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Journal articles====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=B\u00fcchler |first1=Yehoshua |title=The deportation of Slovakian Jews to the Lublin District of Poland in 1942 |journal=[[Holocaust and Genocide Studies]] |date=1991 |volume=6 |issue=2 |pages=151\u2013166 |doi=10.1093/hgs/6.2.151 |language=en |issn=8756-6583 |ref=harv|authorlink=Yehoshua B\u00fcchler}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=B\u00fcchler |first1=Yehoshua |title=First in the Vale of Affliction: Slovakian Jewish Women in Auschwitz, 1942 |journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies |date=1996 |volume=10 |issue=3 |pages=299\u2013325 |doi=10.1093/hgs/10.3.299 |issn=8756-6583|ref=harv}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Cichopek-Gajraj |first1=Anna |title=Limits to \"Jewish power\": how Slovak Jewish leaders negotiated restitution of property after the Second World War |journal=East European Jewish Affairs |date=2014 |volume=44 |issue=1 |page