e\u0161enia \"\u017eidovskej ot\u00e1zky\" na Slovensku v rokoch 1938\u20131945|trans-title=The phenomenon of corruption in the so-called solutions to the \"Jewish questions\" in Slovakia between 1938 and 1945 |pp=96\u2013112 |journal=Forum Historiae |date=2011 |volume=5 |issue=2 |url=http://www.forumhistoriae.sk/sk/clanok/fenomen-korupcie-v-procese-tzv-riesenia-zidovskej-otazky-na-slovensku-v-rokoch-1938-1945 |ref={{sfnref|Kamenec|2011b}} |language=sk |issn=1337-6861}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Kub\u00e1tov\u00e1 |first1=Hana |last2=L\u00e1n\u00ed\u010dek |first2=Jan |title=Jews and Gentiles in Central and Eastern Europe during the Holocaust in history and memory |journal=Holocaust Studies |date=2017|volume=23 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=1\u201316 |doi=10.1080/17504902.2016.1209838|ref=harv|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/310824429}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Legge |first1=Jerome S. |title=Collaboration, Intelligence, and the Holocaust: Ferdinand \u010eur\u010dansk\u00fd, Slovak Nationalism, and the Gehlen Organization |journal=Holocaust and Genocide Studies |date=2018 |volume=32 |issue=2 |pages=224\u2013248 |doi=10.1093/hgs/dcy029|ref=harv|issn=8756-6583}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=L\u00f4n\u010d\u00edkov\u00e1 |first1=Michala |title=Was the antisemitic propaganda a catalyst for tensions in the Slovak-Jewish relations? |journal=Holocaust Studies |date=2017 |volume=23 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=76\u201398 |doi=10.1080/17504902.2016.1209839 |ref=harv}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first1=Eduard |title=The discussions of Nazi Germany on the deportation of Jews in 1942 \u2013 the examples of Slovakia, Rumania and Hungary |url=http://www.historickycasopis.sk/pdf/HCsupplement2011.pdf|journal=Historick\u00fd \u010dasopis |date=2011 |volume=59 |issue=Supplement |pages=111\u2013136 |ref=harv |issn=0018-2575}}\n:{{cite journal |last1=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first1=Eduard |title=On Relations between the Slovak Majority and Jewish Minority During World Wa