ian special edition (Bonus [[Video CD|AVCD]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/release/elephunk-bonus-cd-mr0001265092 |title=Elephunk [Bonus CD&#93; - The Black Eyed Peas &#124; Release Information, Reviews and Credits |publisher=AllMusic |date=2004-05-25 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n| title1          = Where Is the Love?\n| note1           = video\n| title2          = Shut Up\n| note2           = video\n| title3          = Where Is the Love?\n| note3           = instrumental\n| title4          = Shut Up\n| note4           = instrumental\n| title5          = Sumthin for That Ass\n| note5           = non-LP version\n| title6          = Tell Your Mama Come\n| note6           = live\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = yes\n| headline        = France bonus tracks<ref>{{cite web|author=Black Eyed Peas |url=https://www.amazon.fr/Elephunk-Black-Eyed-Peas/dp/B0000ZSA2A |title=Elephunk: Black Eyed Peas: Amazon.fr: Musique |publisher=Amazon.fr |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n| title15         = Hands Up\n| note15          = Live from the [[House of Blues]], Chicago\n| length15        = 5:07\n| title16         = Fly Away\n| note16          = Live from the House of Blues, Chicago\n| length16        = 3:09\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = yes\n| headline        = German bonus track\n| title15         = The Elephunk Theme\n| length15        = 5:05\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n;Black Eyed Peas\n*[[will.i.am]] - vocals on all tracks except 11; [[Moog synthesizer]]s on tracks 1, 4, 5, 8, 9, 10, 11 and 13; drum [[Programming (music)|programming]] on tracks 1, 4, 6, 7, 8, 9 and 10; [[clavinet]] on tracks 12 and 13; drums and piano on track 2; [[Wurlitzer electric piano]] on track 4; synthesizer on track 10; [[Executive producer|executive production]]; production; [[Audio engineering|engineering]] on tracks 2, 3, 4, 8, 9, 12 and 14; [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]] on tracks 10 and 14\n*[[apl.de.ap]] - vocals on tracks 1, 2, 3, 6, 7, 11, 12