cks 1, 5, 6, 7 and 13\n*[[Tony Maserati]] \u2013 mixing on all tracks except 10 and 12\n*[[Brian Gardner|Brian \"Big Bass\" Gardner]] \u2013 [[Audio mastering|mastering]]\n{{col-2}}\n;Additional production personnel\n*Tal Herzberg \u2013 additional engineering on tracks 5 and 13\n*Jun Ishizeki \u2013 engineering on track 10\n*Jason Villaroman \u2013 engineering on track 11\n*[[Chris Lord-Alge]] \u2013 mixing on track 12\n{{col-end}}\n\nThe album is considered a victim of the [[loudness war]], with the worst possible ranking in the Hall of CD Clipping Shame, as 1 minute 19 seconds of the CD's audio has been damaged by clipping.<ref>{{cite web|title=CD Hall of Clipping Shame|url=http://www.cutestudio.net/data/products/audio/CD_clipping/shame/index.php|accessdate=9 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2003-2004)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{albumchart|Australia|1|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|album=Elephunk|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Austria|3|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|album=Elephunk|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 13, 2004}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canadian Albums ([[Jam!]])\n| 2\n|-\n{{albumchart|Denmark|3|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|album=Elephunk|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Netherlands|5|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|album=Elephunk|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Finland|3|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|album=Elephunk|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|France|2|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|album=Elephunk|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| German Albums ([[GfK Entertainment Charts|Offizielle Top 100]])<ref name=\"Mariah charts\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mariah-charts.com/chartdata/PBlackEyedPeas.htm |title=Chart Data: Black Eyed Peas |publisher=Mariah-charts.com |accessdate=Ma