ol\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Edition\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canada<ref>{{cite web|author=Black Eyed Peas (Artist) |url=https://www.amazon.ca/Elephunk-Black-Eyed-Peas/dp/B00009V7RF |title=Elephunk: Black Eyed Peas: Amazon.ca: Music |publisher=Amazon.ca |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n| June 24, 2003\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Standard\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Universal Music Group|Universal]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Germany<ref>{{cite web|author=The Black Eyed Peas |url=https://www.amazon.de/Elephunk-Black-Eyed-Peas/dp/B00009V7RF |title=Elephunk: Amazon.de: Musik |publisher=Amazon.de |date=2009-09-09 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n| July 1, 2003\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United Kingdom<ref name=\"amazon.co.uk\">{{cite web|author=The Black Eyed Peas |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Elephunk-Explicit-Lyrics-Black-Eyed/dp/B0000ATU53 |title=Elephunk [Explicit Lyrics&#93;: Amazon.co.uk: Music |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n| August 7, 2003\n| [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States<ref name=\"amazon.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Elephunk-Black-Eyed-Peas/dp/B00029LNHS |title=Elephunk: Music |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n| May 26, 2004\n| Re-issue\n| A&M\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|20em}}\n\n{{The Black Eyed Peas}}\n\n[[Category:2003 albums]]\n[[Category:The Black Eyed Peas albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Ron Fair]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by will.i.am]]\n[[Category:Interscope Geffen A&M Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "31.0.34.232", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eWeekly charts)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elephunk"}
{"title_page": "Hey Mama (The Black Eyed Peas song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2004 single by The Black Eyed Peas}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Hey Mama\n| cover      = Black Eyed Peas - Hey Mama - CD cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[The Black Eyed Peas]] featuring [[Tippa Irie]]\n| album      = [[Elephunk]]\n| released   = {{start date|df=y|2004|02|10}}\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 2003\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[dancehall]] \n| length     = 3:35 <small>(Album Version)</small> <br /> 4:12 <small>(Single Version)</small> <br /> 3:45 <small>(Radio Edit)</small>\n| label      = [[A&M Records|A&M]], [[will.i.am Music Group|will.i.am]], [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| writer     = [[will.i.am|Will Adams]], [[Tippa Irie|Anthony Henry]]\n| producer   = [[will.i.am]]\n| chronology = [[The Black Eyed Peas]] Singles\n| prev_title = [[Shut Up (The Black Eyed Peas song)|Shut Up]]\n| prev_year  = 2003\n| next_title = [[Let's Get It Started]]\n| next_year  = 2004\n}}\n\n\"'''Hey Mama'''\" is a song by the American band [[the Black Eyed Peas]]. It reached #23 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 chart. The 2003 single is the third one taken from their 2003 album ''[[Elephunk]]''.\n\n== Song information ==\n\"Hey Mama\" was released in 2004 as the album's third single, and was a moderate hit. The song features vocals from British reggae singer [[Tippa Irie]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.encartespop.com.br/2010/05/encarte-black-eyed-peas-elephunk.html | title=Elephunk CD Booklet (Encartes Pop) | accessdate=2017-11-13}}</ref> The single version of the song differs from the album version in that it cuts a verse from the end of the song and replaces it with an entirely new one performed by members [[Taboo (rapper)|Taboo]] and [[apl.de.ap]] (both of whom didn't perform on the original album version), changes some of the lyrics, and slightly alters the instrumentals.\n\nThe song was featured in the original television commercial for the [[iPod]]. \"Hey Mama\" reached #3 in Switzerland, and #4 in Australia, Austria and New Zealand. It reached #6 in the UK becoming their third top ten hit there, and was also a success in Canada and the US, reaching #9 and #23 respectively. The song was featured in 2007 in Konami's Dance Dance Revolution Ultramix 3 on the Xbox gaming system.\n\nThe song was used to promote the [[2004 in film|2004]] film ''[[Garfield: The Movie]]'' which stars [[Bill Murray]] voicing the titular role. In the film, Garfield has a dance off with Odie to the song, which was included on the film's soundtrack and was used in advertisements for the film.\n\nA college band version of the song was in the soundtrack for ''[[NCAA March Madness 2005]]''.\n\n==Music video==\n[[Image:HeyMamaVideo.png|thumb|left|The Black Eyed Peas in the psychedelic limbo from the music video.]]\n\nThe music video features 3 main locations, the first shown being a psychedelic limbo, where the BEP does breakdancing and the main verse of the song is sung. (Hey Mama, this that beat that make you move, mama). The color scheme is mostly yellow, red, brown and off-white. The second is the vertically-black-and-white striped canvas-room. A few parts are sung in here, but the main one is the one featuring [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]]. The third one is the club dance scene, which has lots of background characters dancing. \n{{clear}}\n\n==Track listing==\n;CD single\n#\"Hey Mama\"\n#\"Positivity\" (Live From House of Blues, Chicago)\n#\"Release\" (Live From House of Blues, Chicago)\n#\"Hey Mama\" - The Video\n\n==Personnel==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n;The Black Eyed Peas\n*[[will.i.am]] &ndash; [[Singing|vocals]], [[Moog synthesizer]], [[Drum kit|drum]] [[Programming (music)|programming]], [[Wurlitzer electric piano]], [[Executive producer|executive production]], [[Record producer|production]], [[Audio engineering|engineering]]\n*[[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]] &ndash; vocals\n*[[Taboo (rapper)|Taboo]] &ndash; vocals (only on the single/radio version)\n*[[apl.de.ap]] &ndash; vocals (only on the single/radio version)\n{{col-3}}\n;Additional musicians\n*[[Tippa Irie]] &ndash; vocals\n*[[Dante Santiago]] &ndash; [[Backing vocalist|backing vocals]]\n{{col-3}}\n;Production personnel\n*[[Ron Fair]] &ndash; executive production\n*[[Tony Maserati]] &ndash; [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]]\n*[[Brian Gardner]] &ndash; [[Audio mastering|mastering]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2004)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|4|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|4|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|6|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|25|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Denmark|8|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|18|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Finland|14|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|5|artist=Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama|songid=6067}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Hungary|26|week=30|year=2004}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Hungarytop10|5|week=13|year=2004}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|5|song=Hey Mama|access-date=January 20, 2020}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Italy|8|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|5|year=2004|week=14|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|6|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|4|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|6|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| Poland ([[Polish Singles Chart]])<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071024120827/http://www.pifpaf.com.pl/airplay/lista_21_2004.html|title=Nielsen Music Control|archivedate=2007-10-24 |url=http://www.nielsenmusiccontrol.com/index_pol}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|23\n|-\n|Russia ([[Tophit|Top Radio Hits]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tophit.ru/ru/tracks/716/|title=The Black Eyed Peas - Hey Mama\n|publisher=[[Tophit]] |accessdate=22 June 2018}}</ref> \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|106\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|5|date=2004-03-14}} \n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|3|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|song=Hey Mama}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|6|date=2004-03-14}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKrandb|2|date=2004-03-14}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|23|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|artistid=272581}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardpopsongs|8|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|artistid=272581}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardrhythmic|27|artist=The Black Eyed Peas|artistid=272581}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2004)\n!Position\n|-\n|Australia (ARIA)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/annual-charts/2004/singles-chart|title=ARIA End of Year Singles Chart 2004|publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|42\n|-\n|Austria (\u00d63 Austria Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://austriancharts.at/year.asp?cat=s&id=2004|title=Jahreshitparade Singles 2004|website=austriancharts.at|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|42\n|-\n|Belgium (Ultratop Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=2004|title=Jaaroverzichten 2004|publisher=Ultratop|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|44\n|-\n|Belgium (Ultratop Wallonia)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/fr/annual.asp?year=2004|title=Rapports Annuels 2004|publisher=Ultratop|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|96\n|-\n|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-2004|title=Top 100 Single-Jahrescharts|language=German|work=GfK Entertainment|publisher=offiziellecharts.de|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|47\n|-\n|Hungary (R\u00e1di\u00f3s Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zene.slagerlistak.hu/archivum/eves-osszesitett-listak/radios/2004|title=R\u00e1di\u00f3s Top 100 - hallgatotts\u00e1gi adatok alapj\u00e1n - 2004|accessdate=3 April 2020|publisher=[[Mahasz]]}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|95\n|-\n|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/2004|title=Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 2004|publisher=Dutch Top 40|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|57\n|-\n|Netherlands (Single Top 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=2004&cat=s|title=Jaaroverzichten \u2013 Single 2004|website=dutchcharts.nl|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|75\n|-\n|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/charts/jahreshitparade/2004|title=Schweizer Jahreshitparade 2004|website=hitparade.ch|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|27\n|-\n|UK Singles (Official Charts Company)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukchartsplus.co.uk/ChartsPlusYE2004.pdf|title=UK Year-End Chart 2004|format=PDF|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|79\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://billboardtop100of.com/2004-2/|title=Billboard Top 100 \u2013 2004|website=billboardtop100of.com|accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|95\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{youtube|A0aYaX6j5hM|Music video for \"Hey Mama\"}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090426084129/http://www.younnta.com/2009/04/23/black-eyed-peas-hey-mama-lyrics-music-video/ Hey Mama (lyrics , video)]\n* {{MetroLyrics song|black-eyed-peas|hey-mama}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider 