{"title_page": "Bob Bain", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Bob Bain\n| background          = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date|mf=y|1924|01|26}}\n| birth_place         = Chicago, Illinois, U.S.\n| death_date          = {{death date and age|mf=y|2018|06|21|1924|01|26}} \n| death_place          = [[Oxnard, California]], U.S.\n| genre               = [[Jazz]], pop, rock\n| occupation          = Musician, composer\n| instrument          = Guitar\n| years_active        = 1940s\u20132010s\n| label               = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n}}\n\n'''Bob Bain''' (26 January 1924 \u2013 21 June 2018) was an American guitarist mainly known for his film music contributions.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/bob-bain-mn0000215947/biography |title=Bob Bain |first=Eugene |last=Chadbourne |website=AllMusic |accessdate=2019-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fretboardjournal.com/columns/remembering-bob-bain-1924-2018 |title=Remembering Bob Bain: 1924 \u2013 2018 |first=Adam |last=Levy |website=Fretboard Journal |accessdate=2019-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vintageguitar.com/2810/bob-bain |title=Bob Bain - The Silent Giant |first=Jim |last=LaDiana |website=Vintage Guitar |accessdate=2019-02-25}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n* 1958: ''Rockin' Rollin' Strollin' '' ([[Capitol Records|Capitol]])\n* 1960: ''Latin Love''\t(Capitol)\n* 1960: ''Guitar De Amor''\t(Capitol)\n* 2014: ''The Guitars of Bob Bain'' (Blue Moon Producciones Discogr\u00e1ficas S.L.)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0047727 Bob Bain entry at IMDb]\n \n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bain, Bob}}\n[[Category:1924 births]]\n[[Category:2018 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American guitarists]]\n[[Category:American jazz guitarists]]\n[[Category:American music arrangers]]\n[[Category:American session musicians]]\n[[Category:Contemporary Records artists]]\n[[Category:Jazz musicians from Illinois]]\n[[Category:People from Chicago]]\n[[Category:West Coast jazz guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:Mainstream jazz guitarists]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male musicians]]\n[[Category:Male jazz musicians]]\n\n\n{{US-jazz-guitarist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Bob Bain\n| background          = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date|mf=y|1924|01|26}}\n| birth_place         = Chicago, Illinois, U.S.\n| death_date          = {{death date and age|mf=y|2018|06|21|1924|01|26}} \n| death_place          = [[Oxnard, California]], U.S.\n| genre               = [[Jazz]], pop, rock\n| occupation          = Musician, composer\n| instrument          = Guitar\n| years_active        = 1940s\u20132010s\n| label               = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n}}\n\n'''Bob Bain''' (26 January 1924 - 21 June 2018) was an American guitarist mainly known for his film music contributions.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/bob-bain-mn0000215947/biography |title=Bob Bain |first=Eugene |last=Chadbourne |website=AllMusic |accessdate=2019-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fretboardjournal.com/columns/remembering-bob-bain-1924-2018 |title=Remembering Bob Bain: 1924 \u2013 2018 |first=Adam |last=Levy |website=Fretboard Journal |accessdate=2019-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vintageguitar.com/2810/bob-bain |title=Bob Bain - The Silent Giant |first=Jim |last=LaDiana |website=Vintage Guitar |accessdate=2019-02-25}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n* 1958: ''Rockin' Rollin' Strollin' '' ([[Capitol Records|Capitol]])\n* 1960: ''Latin Love''\t(Capitol)\n* 1960: ''Guitar De Amor''\t(Capitol)\n* 2014: ''The Guitars of Bob Bain'' (Blue Moon Producciones Discogr\u00e1ficas S.L.)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0047727 Bob Bain entry at IMDb]\n \n{{Authority control}}\n